 Smith于1457年出生在英国英格兰坎布利其爾坎布利其。她和Charles Chard Francis Sterne至少有1个儿子。她去世于1521年在英国英格兰坎布利其爾享年64岁。"},"hr":{"1457–1521":"1457.–1521.","1455–1510":"1455–1510","1475–1521":"1475.–1521.","1457":"1457.","1521":"1521.","1510":"1510","1455":"1455","1475":"1475.","Abt 1510":"oko 1510.","Hastingfield, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridgeshire, Engleska, United Kingdom","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Engleska, United Kingdom","Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England":"Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1457–1521":"1457–1521","1455–1510":"1455–1510","1475–1521":"1475–1521","1457":"1457","1521":"1521","1510":"1510","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","Abt 1510":"okolo 1510","Hastingfield, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridgeshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England":"Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, Anglie","England, United Kingdom":"Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1457–1521":"1457–1521","1455–1510":"1455–1510","1475–1521":"1475–1521","1457":"1457","1521":"1521","1510":"1510","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","Abt 1510":"omkring 1510","Hastingfield, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England":"Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1457–1521":"1457–1521","1455–1510":"1455–1510","1475–1521":"1475–1521","1457":"1457","1521":"1521","1510":"1510","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","Abt 1510":"circa 1510","Hastingfield, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridgeshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England":"Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1457–1521":"1457–1521","1455–1510":"1455–1510","1475–1521":"1475–1521","1457":"1457","1521":"1521","1510":"1510","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","Abt 1510":"about 1510","Hastingfield, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom","Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England":"Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Smith","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: occupational name denoting a worker in metal, especially iron, such as a blacksmith or farrier, from Middle English <i>smith</i> ‘smith’ (Old English <i>smith</i>, probably a derivative of <i>smītan</i> ‘to strike, hammer’). Early examples are also found in the Latin form   Faber  . Metal-working was one of the earliest occupations for which specialist skills were required, and its importance ensured that this term and its equivalents in other languages were the most widespread of all occupational surnames in Europe. Medieval smiths were important not only in making horseshoes, plowshares, and other domestic articles, but above all for their skill in forging swords, other weapons, and armor. This is also the most frequent of all surnames in the US. It is very common among African Americans and Native Americans (see also 5 below). This surname (in any of the two possible English senses; see also below) is also found in Haiti. See also   Smither  .","English: from Middle English <i>smithe</i> ‘smithy, forge’ (Old English <i>smiththe</i>). The surname may be topographic, for someone who lived in or by a blacksmith's shop, occupational, for someone who worked in one, or habitational, from a place so named, such as Smitha in King's Nympton (Devon). Compare   Smithey  .","Irish and Scottish: sometimes adopted for Gaelic <b>Mac Gobhann</b>, Irish <b>Mac Gabhann</b> ‘son of the smith’. See   McGowan  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Smithe","meanings":["(1997: 115;2007: 306; 2010: NA)","English: variant of   Smith  ."]},{"name":"Smither","meanings":["English (Surrey): occupational name from Middle English <i>smith(i)ere</i>, <i>smeth(i)ere</i> ‘blacksmith’, a derivative of Middle English <i>smithen</i>, <i>smethen</i>, ‘to make (something) in metal, to forge’. Compare   Smith  ."]},{"name":"Smithey","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): from Middle English <i>smithi</i> ‘smithy, forge’ (Old Norse <i>smithja</i>), used either as a topographic name for someone who lived in or by a blacksmith's shop, or an occupational name for someone who worked in one. Compare   Smith   and   Smead  ."]},{"name":"Smyth","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Ronan, Aidan, Brigid, Conor, Eoin, Malachy, Paddy.","English: variant of   Smith  . This form of the surname is particularly common Ireland."]},{"name":"Smythe","meanings":["English (London): variant of   Smith  ."]},{"name":"McGowan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Siobhan, Cormac, Seamus, Aileen, Colm, Eithne, Kieran, Niall, Paddy.","Scottish and Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac (a') Ghobhainn</b> or <b>Mac Gobhann</b> (Scottish) or <b>Mac (an) Ghabhann</b> (Irish), ‘son of (the) smith’. This name has also been Anglicized as   Smith   and   Smithson  ."]},{"name":"Smead","meanings":["English:","occupational name from Middle English <i>smeth(e)</i> ‘smith’, a phonetic variant of   Smith   1 that was widespread in medieval England, especially in south-eastern and south-western counties.","topographic, occupational, and habitational name from Middle English <i>smethe</i> ‘smithy, forge’ (Old English <i>smethe</i>), a side form of   Smith   2, for someone who lived and worked at a blacksmith's, or who lived in or came from a place so named, such as Smeeth (Kent) or Smeed Farm in Hastingleigh (Kent). Compare the synonymous   Smithey  ."]},{"name":"Faber","meanings":["German, Dutch, French (Alsace and Lorraine), and Danish; Slovak and Czech (mainly <b>Fáber</b>): occupational name from Latin <i>faber</i> ‘blacksmith’. At the time of the Reformation, it was much used as a humanistic name, a translation into Latin of vernacular surnames such as German   Schmidt   and Dutch   Smit  . Compare   Fabri   and   Fauber  .","History: In North America, this surname was originally also part of a title. It was François Lefebvre, <i>sieur</i> Duplessis Faber from Paris, France, whose title <i>sieur Duplessis Faber</i> was shortened into the surname <i>Faber</i>. He married Marie-Madeleine Chorel in Champlain, QC, in 1689."]}]},{"name":"Dorothy","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Usual English form of   Dorothea .  The name was not used in the Middle Ages, but was taken up in the 15th century and became common thereafter. It was borne by the American film star  Dorothy Lamour  (  1914–1996 , born  Dorothy Kaumeyer )."],"variants":[{"name":"Dorothee","meanings":["Usual English form of   Dorothea .  The name was not used in the Middle Ages, but was taken up in the 15th century and became common thereafter. It was borne by the American film star  Dorothy Lamour  (  1914–1996 , born  Dorothy Kaumeyer )."]},{"name":"Dorothie","meanings":["Usual English form of   Dorothea .  The name was not used in the Middle Ages, but was taken up in the 15th century and became common thereafter. It was borne by the American film star  Dorothy Lamour  (  1914–1996 , born  Dorothy Kaumeyer )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Dorothy Smith was born in 1457, in Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Charles Chard Francis Sterne. She died in 1521, in Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1457–1521":"1457–1521","1455–1510":"1455–1510","1475–1521":"1475–1521","1457":"1457","1521":"1521","1510":"1510","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","Abt 1510":"umbes 1510","Hastingfield, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England":"Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1457–1521":"1457–1521","1455–1510":"1455–1510","1475–1521":"1475–1521","1457":"1457","1521":"1521","1510":"1510","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","Abt 1510":"noin 1510","Hastingfield, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England":"Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1457–1521":"1457–1521","1455–1510":"1455–1510","1475–1521":"1475–1521","1457":"1457","1521":"1521","1510":"1510","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","Abt 1510":"environ 1510","Hastingfield, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cambridgeshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Cambridge, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"Canteburge, Cambridgeshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, England":"Haslingfield, Cambridgeshire, Angleterre","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Dorothy Smith est née en 1457, à Canteburge, Cambridgeshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Charles Chard Francis Sterne. Elle est décédée en 1521, à Cambridgeshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 64 ans."},"de":{"1457–1521":"1457–1521","1455–1510":"1455–1510","1475–1521":"1475–1521","1457":"1457","1521":